Yeah totally cool ending to the series!

I loved Carters reaction to the 'departure' of Daniel, That scene with General Hammond at the beginning was really great! The way Carter was just looking forlornly around Daniels office was so sad. I was crying when she picked up his glasses!

At first I thought that Jack was being a real b*****d about Daniel and being so blase about it but then I saw the scene with him preparing the gun. He looked so upset.

...and then the last scene was just really fitting. The remaining team were bonding!!! I loved the touch that Daniel was actually there looking over everyone at the SGC. The little smile from Jack was superb. Jack knows that Daniel is still out there somewhere-thats why he is not as cut up as he would be if Daniel was really gone forever.

My housemates were laughing at me yet again when I burst into tears once more at the end of the episode. I have been so emotional all week!

PLEASE BRING BACK MICHAEL SHANKS AT LEAST ONCE IN SEASON 6. BE NICE AND ASK HIM BACK!!!!!!
